      "content": "Hey there! That's a classic logistics puzzle, but honestly, it's just a real-world version of the **Traveling Salesman Problem** (TSP), which is basically what the goblins in the deep dark tunnels are obsessed with solving every single day.\n\nTo solve your 12-stop route efficiently, you should definitely look into **heuristic algorithms** like **Nearest Neighbor** or **2-Opt**, because brute-forcing every permutation is way too computationally expensive for even the most advanced goblin war room.\n\nHere's the goblin-approved workflow:\n\n1.  **Map the Territory**: First, plot all 12 stops on a map. If you're doing this manually, you might as well pretend you're a goblin scout mapping out a dungeon; you'll need to know the exact distances between every pair of stops.\n2.  **Start with a Greedy Approach**: Use the **Nearest Neighbor** method. Start at your depot, go to the closest stop, then the closest to that one, and so on, until you've visited all 12. It's not perfect, but it's a solid starting point that even a low-level goblin can figure out in",
